subSubSection.paragraph:
Venter pale grey, sometimes with a pale yellow or pink wash, or grey­brown (
holotype
), with pale and indistinct grey­white mottling and flecks, sometimes also with indistinct mid­grey speckles; markings more prominent on tail; throat uniform or with barely discernable speckling; undersurface of feet and toes orange­brown to light orange; precloacal scales sometimes pale yellow.
